Description:
# Upgraded to Visual Studio 2012
# Added *BidirctionalPathfinder* class that runs 2-3 times faster than previous using:
## A (serial) implementation of New Parallel Bidirectional A*;
## Heap-on-Top priority queue implementation; 
## A 32x32 *LayeredBoardStorage* class that improves caching of board details;
## A few scattered miscellaneous code improvements
# Additional basic functionality pushed into the *HexBoard* utility class from the examples, including the *BoardStorage.* abstraction discussed above.

This faster A* implementation decreases the time for my most complex case (two long diagonals on a 750 x 420 terrain map) from 0.86 and 1.55 seconds to 0.43 seconds. Total nodes expanded decreases from 160,000 and 230,000 respectively to 80,000, of over 330,000 on the whole board..

The two cases are the same path in opposite directions, so the Bidirectional implementation now merges them to the same test case.

# Rearranged namespaces and folder locations for better navigation;
# Added an example of Path-type selection to HexgridExample2;
# Eliminated (need for) NaviagableBoard and FovBoard methods in IHexBoard;
# Rolled Coords.cs into HexCoords.cs and eliminated the base class Coords.cs;
# Renamed IPath2, Path2 and PathFinder2 back to IPath, Path, and PathFinder, as new namespace guareantees uniqueness vs old implementations;
# Tidy up Debug Tracing;
# Prevent inadvertent client overwrite of FOV details by making setter internal-access only; and
# Removed old Version 4 example and library.

1) Added TerrainMap example;
2) Added demonstration of Shadow-Casting Field-of-View on both maps; and
3) Removed reference web pages out of source download to make it a more reasonable size.

1) Abstracted MapBoard and MapDisplay functionality into separate classes;
2) Corrected PathFinder to use -1 as Impassable flag instead of 999;
3) Added demonstration of simple map transposition to HexGridExample; and
4) Code clean-up for better exposition of principles.

# Finished pushing functionality from HexgridExample into HexPanel;
# Expanded Doxygen documentation considerably, including class diagrams;  
# Enabled freezing of FOV with a Range-Line to verify line-of-sight; 
# Implemented Async versions of GetPath and GetFOV;
# Fixed display performance from nesting a call to SystemFonts; and
# Numerous additional small enhancements and tidy-up.
